720.question: How much is proposed model better than baselines in performed experiments?
720.response: {'Answer': 'The proposed GDP model outperforms baselines E2ECM and CDM in all evaluation metrics including BLEU, AP@R, and time cost on both DSTC2 and Maluuba datasets. Compared with the best baseline E2ECM+RL, the proposed GDP+RL model achieves comparable performance on DSTC2, and outperforms on Maluuba dataset.'}
720.answer:
most of the models have similar performance on BPRA: DSTC2 (+0.0015), Maluuba (+0.0729)
GDP achieves the best performance in APRA: DSTC2 (+0.2893), Maluuba (+0.2896)
GDP significantly outperforms the baselines on BLEU: DSTC2 (+0.0791), Maluuba (+0.0492)
